    "Liu et al. (2018b) proposed a GAN-based curriculum learning strategy.",
    "The proposed method contains two stages.",
    "First, the model is trained using the original data and then with more complex data consisting of GANgenerated images.",
    "Li et al. (2021c) utilized CycleGan (Zhu et al. 2017) for the augmentation of rare taxa, and Khan et al. (2022); Ali et al. (2022) applied DC-GAN (Radford et al. 2015) to augment an algae image dataset.",
    "Vallez et al. (2022) compared data augmentation by combining two diatom images from the same class using morphing and image registration methods performing diffeomorphic transformations to generation of synthetic images by a GAN."
